Mars Odyssey - HEND, HETE - FREGATE, and Konus-Wind observed this short
(~180 ms) burst at 60748 s.  We have triangulated it to a preliminary,
3 sigma error box whose area is ~ 6700 sq.  arcmin. and whose
coordinates are:

        RA(2000)                 DEC(2000)
 11 h 29 m 28.34 s     42 o 54 '   4.77 "  (CENTER)
 11 h 48 m 39.60 s     39 o 41 '  53.44 "  (CORNER)
 11 h 48 m 26.73 s     39 o 28 '  28.57 "  (CORNER)
 11 h  7 m 54.94 s     45 o 22 '  35.24 "  (CORNER)
 11 h  7 m 52.77 s     45 o 10 '  47.92 "  (CORNER)
 
As this error box lies far from the Galactic plane, this
event is most likely a short-duration, hard-spectrum GRB,
rather than an SGR.

Because the Mars Odyssey response is rather weak (~3 sigma),
confirmation of this position from a fourth spacecraft will
be required.  

